review.reviewBody:
I agree with what Katie and Eric wrote, quoted below; the plates and bowls lose utility due to fact they do not nest in one another. Whether camping, or at home, each plate or bowl takes up space and cannot be stacked into each other. Not even the heaviest dishware I know of has that problem. MSR is one of the most important outdoor gear companies, manufacturing the best stoves, and other gear. Cookwear also the best available. These plates and bowls are great, but, not being able to stack them is a real detractor. I bought three each of a two bowls and plates, am glad I did, but, they take up the space of like 20 full size bowls or plates in my kitchen cabinet. Presumably MSR has considered this and determined that the product is best as is, maybe ? Personally, I vote for nesting/stackable versions, similar to any old school tupperware. 

&quot;I love that these nest with MSR&apos;s cook pots, it&apos;s a great size and nice that it&apos;s deep; BUT, I feel like they could be just slightly sloped to be able to stack into each other, and still nest within MSR&apos;s pots. That tweak would honestly make these great.&quot;
 (Katie on 24 Aug 2021)

&quot;Deep Dish Plates That Don&apos;t Nest&apos; Review by Eric on 22 Jul 2019 review stating &quot;Deep Dish Plates That Don&apos;t Nest Great wall height proportional to diameter! Perfect bottom &amp; wall thickness to support the weight of food without being so thick that they add too much weight. Really wish the same diameter plates (and bowls) nested within each other. Plates nesting inside one another is far more important to me than nesting with a pot. When the family goes caDeep Dish Plates That Don&apos;t Nestmping I now have one plate that nests with a pot and other plates that take up a ton of room that nest with nothing. For those who will never buy more than one plate (or bowl) these are great in nesting with MSR&apos;s pots but for those who have more than one person and therefore more than one plate (or bowl) you can do better taking up less space with nesting plates. This product&apos;s description really should state in all capital letters that the plates will not nest with each other. &quot;
